section.section:
The following persons may hunt the specified game birds and mammals on Sundays:
A person using State certified raptors to hunt game birds or mammals during open season;
An unarmed person participating in an organized fox chase to chase foxes;
Provided that the provisions of § 10-906(b)(3) of this title are met, a person:
Using a regulated shooting ground under § 10-906 of this title to hunt the following pen-reared game birds:
Having the written permission of the owner of the land or other person designated by the owner of the land, if the land is owned or leased by a person other than the person hunting on Sundays;
Subject to the provisions of § 10-411 of this subtitle, in Allegany, Calvert, Caroline, Carroll, Charles, Dorchester, Frederick, Garrett, Harford, St. Mary's, Somerset, Talbot, Washington, Wicomico, and Worcester counties, a person hunting deer on private property with a bow and arrow or crossbow during open season on the last three Sundays in October and the second Sunday in November;
Except on Easter Sunday, in Allegany County and Garrett County, a person hunting turkey on the last Sunday in April and the first Sunday in May; and
In Calvert County, Caroline County, Charles County, Dorchester County, and St. Mary's County, a person hunting turkey on private property on any Sunday during the spring turkey hunting season.
